## Decision Matrix

| Category | Pass | Modify | Block |
|----------|------|--------|-------|
| CPU utilization | < 70% with margin | 70-85% with analysis | > 85% or unanalyzed |
| WCET analysis | Measured on target | Estimated with margin | Not measured |
| ISR latency | Within budget | Tight but bounded | Unbounded |
| Priority inversion | Prevented | Risk documented | Unmitigated |
| Jitter | Within spec | Marginal | Exceeds spec |
| Verification | On-target stress tested | Partial testing | Untested |

---

## Final Verdict

- [ ] **Proceed**: All deadlines are met with documented margin
- [ ] **Modify**: Address timing gaps before implementation
- [ ] **Spike**: Measure on target hardware before committing to design
- [ ] **Escalate**: Safety deadline cannot be guaranteed -- requires architecture change

